data.description: Potentially assumable (low down!) with  interest rate below 4% OR Seller will consider lease-to-own!! This ranch home offers NEW energy efficient windows, an accessible new shower and ramp in garage leading to 2nd bedroom. Privacy door from the master bedrm to the bathroom. Set on a 2-Family residential lot on a dead end, with expansive mountain views from the living room; the Arctic Entrykeeps in the heat, as do the NEW windows! Embrace comfort and energy efficiency with this ranch home, featuring new windows that invite natural light and offer modern insulation. The addition of an arctic entry enhances the home's functionality, providing a welcoming space while helping to keep the cold Alaskan weather at bay.  Enjoy the view of the surrounding mountains right from your living room, setting the tone for the cozy atmosphere found throughout the house. Featuring 3 bedrooms, the third bedroom comes with a door leading directly to the garage, where you'll find a convenient handicap ramp, ensuring easy accessibility for everyone.   Step outside, and you'll discover a conveniently fenced-in yard, creating a safe haven for both children and pets to play freely. The private back patio invites you to unwind and enjoy entertaining guests or simply basking in the tranquility of your own space.  This property is located in an established neighborhood that boasts a short commute to the Alaska Native Hospital or Providence. Bartlett High School offers specialized programs such as a medical academy and Army JrROTC, ensuring excellent educational opportunities for your family. Additionally, the convenience of having a movie theater just a stone's throw away means you can enjoy the latest blockbusters with ease.
